1
00:00:10,733 --> 00:00:12,500
<i> I really heard something.</i>

2
00:00:12,633 --> 00:00:15,400
<i>- Well.
- A knock, a thud.</i>

3
00:00:15,533 --> 00:00:16,900
<i> Where?</i>

4
00:00:17,033 --> 00:00:19,033
<i> What are you doing?</i>

5
00:00:19,167 --> 00:00:20,867
<i>That's why I'm doing this,
remember?</i>

6
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:22,200
<i> For Mookie.</i>

7
00:00:22,333 --> 00:00:25,033
<i>I can't be at peace until
I see what's happening to her.</i>

8
00:00:25,167 --> 00:00:27,300
<i>- Love? Mookie?
- Jade.</i>

9
00:00:27,433 --> 00:00:28,633
<i> What are you doing here?</i>

10
00:00:28,767 --> 00:00:30,467
<i> I've found the culprit.</i>

11
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:33,500
<i> There's a big rat inside.</i>

12
00:00:33,633 --> 00:00:34,333
<i> What's this?</i>

13
00:00:36,133 --> 00:00:37,200
<i> I think this is mine.</i>

14
00:00:37,333 --> 00:00:39,100
<i> Remember that I'm always here</i>

15
00:00:39,233 --> 00:00:40,233
<i>whenever you're not feeling
okay.</i>

16
00:00:40,367 --> 00:00:44,000
<i>I want to show up to you,
but I'm not ready yet.</i>

17
00:00:44,133 --> 00:00:45,967
<i>- Come on, let's eat.
- Yes. This looks delicious.</i>

18
00:00:46,100 --> 00:00:46,767
<i> Emma?</i>

19
00:00:46,900 --> 00:00:48,333
<i> I saw Emma!</i>

20
00:00:48,467 --> 00:00:49,533
<i> I saw my husband and child.</i>

21
00:00:49,667 --> 00:00:51,200
<i> They were happy.</i>

22
00:00:51,333 --> 00:00:52,400
<i> And Jade wasn't there.</i>

23
00:00:52,533 --> 00:00:53,533
<i> Dad!</i>

24
00:00:53,667 --> 00:00:54,733
<i> Dad, what are you doing?</i>

25
00:01:33,167 --> 00:01:34,300
Wake up!

26
00:01:34,433 --> 00:01:36,600
Wake up, witch! Come on!

27
00:01:36,733 --> 00:01:38,067
Wake up!

28
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:39,200
Wake up!

29
00:01:40,500 --> 00:01:41,867
I said wake up!

30
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:43,267
Wake up!

31
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:45,467
Wake up!

32
00:01:45,600 --> 00:01:47,100
Hello!

33
00:01:47,233 --> 00:01:48,767
Are you awake now?

34
00:01:52,300 --> 00:01:56,233
- Wake up! What now?
- Stop.

35
00:01:56,367 --> 00:02:00,100
Stop. Stop, dear. Please stop.

36
00:02:00,233 --> 00:02:01,333
What do you mean stop?

37
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:08,100
That's not enough punishment
for everything you did to me.

38
00:02:08,233 --> 00:02:12,233
Oh, by the way,
it's dinner time.

39
00:02:12,367 --> 00:02:14,167
Are you hungry?

40
00:02:14,333 --> 00:02:16,267
Here.

41
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:18,533
Your writing is so lovely.

42
00:02:18,667 --> 00:02:22,033
So, there. Eat it. Eat it!

43
00:02:22,167 --> 00:02:23,467
I said eat it!

44
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:42,867
Have mercy.

45
00:02:44,567 --> 00:02:48,333
Have mercy. Please stop.

46
00:02:48,500 --> 00:02:49,933
Mercy?

47
00:02:54,400 --> 00:03:01,400
A worthless mother like you
doesn't deserve mercy!

48
00:03:05,700 --> 00:03:08,433
Are you going to expose me
to my husband and child?

49
00:03:08,567 --> 00:03:11,000
Do you plan to ruin my plans?

50
00:03:12,767 --> 00:03:14,633
Are you going to hinder
my happiness?

51
00:03:14,767 --> 00:03:16,367
Is that your plan? Is that it?

52
00:03:17,400 --> 00:03:19,467
I want to help you.

53
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:20,800
Help?

54
00:03:22,333 --> 00:03:23,667
What the heck are you talking
about?

55
00:03:26,100 --> 00:03:28,300
You have a problem.

56
00:03:28,433 --> 00:03:31,000
You need to consult a doctor.

57
00:03:32,333 --> 00:03:33,633
I'll go with you.

58
00:03:33,767 --> 00:03:35,500
I won't leave you.

59
00:03:35,633 --> 00:03:37,433
I'll make it up to you, dear.

60
00:03:37,567 --> 00:03:39,500
- Why?
- I'll make it up to you.

61
00:03:39,633 --> 00:03:41,467
What do you take me for?

62
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:42,967
A crazy person?

63
00:03:43,100 --> 00:03:45,667
I'm not crazy, Ligaya!

64
00:03:45,800 --> 00:03:46,800
You!

65
00:03:46,933 --> 00:03:49,400
You're the crazy one! You!

66
00:03:51,167 --> 00:03:52,600
You!

67
00:04:05,633 --> 00:04:06,633
Emma.

68
00:04:06,767 --> 00:04:08,167
It seems like Danilo saw you.

69
00:04:08,300 --> 00:04:09,233
What?

70
00:04:14,700 --> 00:04:17,967
I saw her here, Mookie.
She was watching us.

71
00:04:18,100 --> 00:04:23,567
Auntie Jade told us that Mom ran
away with another man, remember?

72
00:04:25,033 --> 00:04:26,933
But I saw her here.

73
00:04:27,100 --> 00:04:31,433
Dad, do you think Mom will
return to us?

74
00:04:31,567 --> 00:04:32,467
I don't know.

75
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:34,433
Maybe she wants to explain
herself.

76
00:04:34,567 --> 00:04:36,267
She wants to tell us
what happened to her.

77
00:04:36,400 --> 00:04:38,200
Or maybe she has changed her
mind.

78
00:04:38,333 --> 00:04:40,933
Maybe she wants to return to us.
And make our family whole again.

79
00:04:41,067 --> 00:04:42,933
That's possible. Right?

80
00:04:43,067 --> 00:04:46,067
Dad, are you still hoping?

81
00:04:46,200 --> 00:04:47,667
Yes.

82
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:52,400
I don't... I don't know.
Unless I see her face...

83
00:04:52,533 --> 00:04:56,633
Unless I hear the answers
to my questions...

84
00:04:56,767 --> 00:04:59,200
- I can't be at peace, dear.
- Dad.

85
00:04:59,333 --> 00:05:00,933
Dad, look around.

86
00:05:01,100 --> 00:05:03,267
Look.

87
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:06,000
Do you see any sign of Mom?

88
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:11,033
There's nothing, right?

89
00:05:11,167 --> 00:05:13,567
She didn't return.

90
00:05:13,700 --> 00:05:17,767
And she will never return, Dad.

91
00:05:17,900 --> 00:05:19,667
Mookie.

92
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:21,000
Dad!

93
00:05:22,700 --> 00:05:25,033
Dad, please stop.

94
00:05:26,567 --> 00:05:28,233
Look.

95
00:05:28,367 --> 00:05:31,500
You're just hurting yourself.

96
00:05:31,633 --> 00:05:34,100
You're just hurting me.

97
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:39,033
Please, please, Dad.

98
00:05:39,167 --> 00:05:41,967
I want to forget Mom,

99
00:05:44,333 --> 00:05:47,800
but how can I do that if you
don't want to let go of her?

100
00:05:55,233 --> 00:05:57,133
Why aren't we leaving yet?

101
00:05:57,267 --> 00:06:01,367
Danilo will notice if I start
the car.

102
00:06:04,667 --> 00:06:06,933
Just keep hiding there.

103
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:08,467
Don't make any move.

104
00:06:20,633 --> 00:06:21,400
Sir?

105
00:06:23,933 --> 00:06:25,200
What is it, bro?

106
00:06:25,333 --> 00:06:28,833
I'm looking for a woman, Sir.

107
00:06:28,967 --> 00:06:31,100
Did you see any woman here?

108
00:06:38,633 --> 00:06:39,700
I'm looking for a woman, Sir.

109
00:06:39,833 --> 00:06:42,600
Did you see any woman here?

110
00:06:42,767 --> 00:06:43,667
No.

111
00:06:45,700 --> 00:06:46,800
Okay.

112
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:53,667
Hey!

113
00:06:53,800 --> 00:06:55,500
Do you need anything else?

114
00:06:57,300 --> 00:06:59,333
Nothing more.

115
00:06:59,467 --> 00:07:00,633
I'll go ahead.

116
00:07:22,967 --> 00:07:25,433
Danilo's gone, Emma.

117
00:07:25,567 --> 00:07:26,567
Let's go.

118
00:07:34,567 --> 00:07:35,867
No!

119
00:07:36,000 --> 00:07:37,167
No.

120
00:07:37,300 --> 00:07:39,367
I'm not gonna do this.

121
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:43,333
I won't do this. You know what?

122
00:07:43,467 --> 00:07:46,167
Do you know why I don't kill
you?

123
00:07:46,300 --> 00:07:48,000
Do you?

124
00:07:48,167 --> 00:07:52,167
Because I want you to suffer

125
00:07:53,400 --> 00:08:01,300
like how I suffered from the
people who adopted me!

126
00:08:02,933 --> 00:08:04,200
You know what?

127
00:08:07,667 --> 00:08:12,433
You threw us into one big hell,
Ligaya!

128
00:08:14,167 --> 00:08:20,433
When I was young, I wondered...

129
00:08:26,433 --> 00:08:30,367
does my mom remember me?

130
00:08:36,733 --> 00:08:39,900
Does she think of me?

131
00:08:44,467 --> 00:08:46,567
Of course, she doesn't!

132
00:08:46,700 --> 00:08:49,600
Why?

133
00:08:49,733 --> 00:08:54,200
Because you have Emma!

134
00:08:54,367 --> 00:08:57,867
You gave Emma all the love

135
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:01,667
that Jade and I should've
received, too!

136
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:06,133
No. That's not true.

137
00:09:06,267 --> 00:09:08,767
Every day, dear.

138
00:09:08,900 --> 00:09:11,400
I think about you every day.

139
00:09:11,533 --> 00:09:12,633
No!

140
00:09:12,767 --> 00:09:17,467
I remember you every day.
I've never forgotten about you.

141
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:19,700
Liar!

142
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:21,300
Liar!

143
00:09:21,433 --> 00:09:23,433
Liar!

144
00:09:23,567 --> 00:09:26,433
If you really remember us...

145
00:09:26,567 --> 00:09:28,633
if you really think
about us...

146
00:09:30,033 --> 00:09:32,400
you should've come to see us.

147
00:09:32,533 --> 00:09:35,233
I wish you had come to see
how we were doing.

148
00:09:35,367 --> 00:09:37,533
I wish you checked if we were
still breathing...

149
00:09:37,667 --> 00:09:39,233
if we were still alive.

150
00:09:39,367 --> 00:09:41,000
But you didn't!

151
00:09:41,133 --> 00:09:43,700
I was living a hard life
back then.

152
00:09:43,833 --> 00:09:46,033
I didn't have money.

153
00:09:46,167 --> 00:09:47,100
Nothing.

154
00:09:48,867 --> 00:09:54,100
There was no way to see you,
to find you.

155
00:09:54,233 --> 00:09:55,600
No!

156
00:09:55,733 --> 00:09:58,567
Dear, you're not the only one
who suffered.

157
00:09:58,700 --> 00:10:00,933
I suffered more than you did.

158
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:02,533
Believe me.

159
00:10:02,667 --> 00:10:04,533
I suffered, too.

160
00:10:04,667 --> 00:10:06,367
I suffered, too, not just you.

161
00:10:06,500 --> 00:10:09,267
I don't want to hear your lies!

162
00:10:10,867 --> 00:10:12,267
Shut up!

163
00:10:14,067 --> 00:10:16,700
You didn't love us.

164
00:10:16,833 --> 00:10:19,633
You didn't worry about us.

165
00:10:19,767 --> 00:10:22,967
Because you were busy
with someone else. Right?

166
00:10:23,100 --> 00:10:26,167
You gave all your love to Emma.

167
00:10:26,300 --> 00:10:30,033
I deserve a portion
of that love, Ligaya.

168
00:10:30,167 --> 00:10:34,833
But you denied me of it.

169
00:10:36,833 --> 00:10:38,233
That's not true.

170
00:10:38,367 --> 00:10:40,067
Believe me.

171
00:10:40,200 --> 00:10:42,633
Please listen to me.

172
00:10:42,767 --> 00:10:46,067
I regret giving you and Jade
up for adoption.

173
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:47,367
No.

174
00:10:47,500 --> 00:10:52,367
I suffer from it every day.

175
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:58,967
I begged for love from people
who don't love me.

176
00:10:59,100 --> 00:11:03,067
From people who are not related
to me.

177
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:10,767
I begged them because why?
Because you left me!

178
00:11:12,133 --> 00:11:15,100
You abandoned Jade and me!

179
00:11:15,233 --> 00:11:17,967
You threw us away!

180
00:11:18,100 --> 00:11:21,200
That's what happened, Ligaya!
Admit it!

181
00:11:21,333 --> 00:11:23,500
That's what happened, right?

182
00:11:23,633 --> 00:11:26,100
That's what you did, didn't you?

183
00:11:26,233 --> 00:11:27,733
That's what you did!

184
00:11:27,867 --> 00:11:33,400
Believe me, I regret what I did.
I suffer from it every day.

185
00:11:33,533 --> 00:11:35,433
I love you, believe me.

186
00:11:35,567 --> 00:11:36,600
I love Jade.

187
00:11:36,733 --> 00:11:38,833
I love all my children.

188
00:11:38,967 --> 00:11:40,700
- I regret...
- Shut up!

189
00:11:42,867 --> 00:11:48,333
Your lies won't change my mind.

190
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:52,767
I love you so much, dear.

191
00:11:52,900 --> 00:11:54,700
Believe me.

192
00:11:54,833 --> 00:11:56,633
Don't do that.

193
00:11:56,767 --> 00:11:58,867
Listen, listen to...

194
00:12:09,033 --> 00:12:13,400
Oh, by the way, your favorite
daughter, Emma...

195
00:12:14,933 --> 00:12:16,333
is already dead.

196
00:13:13,100 --> 00:13:14,367
I'm back!

197
00:13:14,500 --> 00:13:16,700
Sorry to keep you waiting.

198
00:13:20,200 --> 00:13:21,900
What's happening?

199
00:13:22,067 --> 00:13:24,233
Didn't you like the food
I ordered?

200
00:13:24,367 --> 00:13:25,800
Do you want me to get something
else?

201
00:13:25,933 --> 00:13:28,100
I'll make another order.
Is Loida still here...

202
00:13:28,233 --> 00:13:30,233
No. No, no. Jade.

203
00:13:30,367 --> 00:13:33,267
I saw Emma earlier.

204
00:13:33,400 --> 00:13:34,967
She was peeking through
the gate.

205
00:13:36,567 --> 00:13:37,600
Emma?

206
00:13:37,733 --> 00:13:39,700
Yes.

207
00:13:39,833 --> 00:13:43,000
Love, maybe you saw it wrong.

208
00:13:43,133 --> 00:13:45,667
Seeing Emma is impossible.

209
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:53,067
<i> Emma?</i>

210
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:55,633
<i> Did Danilo see Emma, too?</i>

211
00:13:55,800 --> 00:13:58,467
<i> Is that woman haunting us?</i>

212
00:14:00,333 --> 00:14:03,500
You're right.
Maybe I saw it wrong.

213
00:14:03,633 --> 00:14:05,733
If who I saw was Emma...

214
00:14:05,867 --> 00:14:06,733
if that was her...

215
00:14:06,867 --> 00:14:08,500
Emma! Emma! Emma!

216
00:14:09,500 --> 00:14:12,967
Can you please stop talking
about her?

217
00:14:13,100 --> 00:14:14,633
- Baby girl.
- Mookie.

218
00:14:14,767 --> 00:14:16,067
Baby girl.

219
00:14:17,467 --> 00:14:18,467
Dear.

220
00:14:20,333 --> 00:14:26,533
Love, we were supposed to have
a nice family dinner.

221
00:14:26,667 --> 00:14:32,933
But you kept talking about Emma
and triggered the kid.

222
00:14:33,100 --> 00:14:35,067
I'm sorry.

223
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:38,233
I'm making it worse
for both of you.

224
00:14:38,367 --> 00:14:40,033
I'm sorry. Sorry, sorry.

225
00:14:40,167 --> 00:14:41,800
What do you mean?

226
00:14:41,933 --> 00:14:43,867
Does Mookie have a problem?

227
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:44,900
Yes, Jade.

228
00:14:45,033 --> 00:14:47,300
She has a problem,
she just doesn't tell us.

229
00:14:47,433 --> 00:14:48,700
But she has.

230
00:14:50,900 --> 00:14:53,567
Don't worry, love.

231
00:14:53,700 --> 00:14:55,333
I'll talk to her.

232
00:15:07,767 --> 00:15:10,233
Emma, here's some water.

233
00:15:11,700 --> 00:15:12,600
Thank you.

234
00:15:12,733 --> 00:15:13,833
I'm okay.

235
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:17,233
Emma.

236
00:15:17,367 --> 00:15:20,267
Logan.

237
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:22,333
Are you okay?

238
00:15:22,467 --> 00:15:25,333
Good thing Danilo didn't see
you.

239
00:15:27,267 --> 00:15:28,167
No.

240
00:15:31,367 --> 00:15:34,233
Let's focus on our plan, okay?

241
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:38,667
You'll drive Jade crazy before
you show up to Mookie.

242
00:15:38,800 --> 00:15:40,633
Okay?

243
00:15:40,767 --> 00:15:44,833
Look at this.

244
00:15:44,967 --> 00:15:50,000
Artemis Pharmacy will launch
Ramirez Lab's new vitamins.

245
00:15:50,133 --> 00:15:51,433
We're going to attend.

246
00:15:54,567 --> 00:15:59,467
That's where I'll haunt
Jade and seduce Danilo.

247
00:16:30,833 --> 00:16:31,800
<i> Mookie!</i>

248
00:16:44,300 --> 00:16:46,567
<i>What if Mookie files
a kidnapping case against you?</i>

249
00:16:46,700 --> 00:16:48,533
<i> We have CCTV evidence.</i>

250
00:16:48,667 --> 00:16:50,033
<i> And you know what, Stacy?</i>

251
00:16:50,167 --> 00:16:52,167
<i>Mookie can also file a bullying
case against you.</i>

252
00:16:52,300 --> 00:16:53,567
<i> She also has a witness.</i>

253
00:16:53,700 --> 00:16:55,300
<i> Me.</i>

254
00:16:55,433 --> 00:16:57,100
<i> You've changed a lot.</i>

255
00:16:57,233 --> 00:16:59,467
<i>You're no longer the Mookie
I know.</i>

256
00:17:12,333 --> 00:17:14,567
What's with the sad face,
baby girl?

257
00:17:19,267 --> 00:17:21,033
Nothing, Auntie.

258
00:17:21,167 --> 00:17:23,100
It's Zayn.

259
00:17:23,233 --> 00:17:26,367
He said he didn't like me
anymore

260
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:28,933
because I've changed a lot.

261
00:17:31,467 --> 00:17:34,333
Don't blame yourself, Mookie.

262
00:17:34,467 --> 00:17:36,433
It's not your fault.

263
00:17:36,567 --> 00:17:40,833
Blame your mother.

264
00:17:40,967 --> 00:17:44,067
You rebelled because Emma
left you.

265
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:46,800
And that's understandable.

266
00:17:46,933 --> 00:17:51,133
You need a mother to guide
and teach you.

267
00:17:52,533 --> 00:17:54,733
And where was Emma when you
needed her?

268
00:17:57,400 --> 00:17:59,033
See, baby girl?

269
00:18:00,300 --> 00:18:03,133
Your mother kept your hopes up.

270
00:18:03,267 --> 00:18:06,633
She made you believe
that she really loves you.

271
00:18:06,767 --> 00:18:11,700
She chose to be with her lover
over you,

272
00:18:11,833 --> 00:18:14,700
whom she hasn't been with
for a long time.

273
00:18:17,200 --> 00:18:19,533
What kind of a mother is that?

274
00:18:25,167 --> 00:18:27,033
I'm so sorry, Mookie.

275
00:18:28,433 --> 00:18:33,800
You know, somehow,
I'm also at fault here.

276
00:18:33,933 --> 00:18:36,567
Because, as your Auntie,

277
00:18:36,700 --> 00:18:39,167
I should've stepped up
and guided you.

278
00:18:39,300 --> 00:18:44,567
You don't need to apologize,
Auntie.

279
00:18:44,700 --> 00:18:46,400
You're a good person.

280
00:18:48,667 --> 00:18:53,967
But Mom is so evil.

281
00:18:56,233 --> 00:19:02,133
I will never forgive everything
she did to me and Dad.

282
00:19:13,033 --> 00:19:14,800
It's okay.

283
00:19:14,933 --> 00:19:16,267
I'm here for you.

284
00:19:20,600 --> 00:19:23,500
Is there enough space
for the activities?

285
00:19:23,633 --> 00:19:24,700
Remember,

286
00:19:24,833 --> 00:19:27,567
this interactive launch ties in
with Activora's promise

287
00:19:27,700 --> 00:19:30,867
to deliver stronger immunity,
limitless energy,

288
00:19:31,033 --> 00:19:32,233
and vibrant vitality.

289
00:19:32,367 --> 00:19:36,633
So, implement everything we have
prepared for the program, okay?

290
00:19:36,767 --> 00:19:38,200
Yes, Miss Jade.

291
00:19:38,333 --> 00:19:41,833
We'll use standing tables
so we can have clear space.

292
00:19:41,967 --> 00:19:43,267
Okay. That's a good idea.

293
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:45,400
Update me when it's ready.
Send me pictures.

294
00:19:45,533 --> 00:19:47,567
I want everything perfect, okay?
I'll see you tonight.

295
00:19:47,700 --> 00:19:48,833
Okay, Ma'am.

296
00:19:55,633 --> 00:19:57,700
Have you already studied
the entire venue?

297
00:20:03,200 --> 00:20:05,033
Yes.

298
00:20:05,167 --> 00:20:06,733
I know where we will go later.

299
00:20:16,167 --> 00:20:17,900
I managed to get a copy
of the program.

300
00:20:20,633 --> 00:20:21,867
First floor clear.

301
00:20:22,000 --> 00:20:23,267
Checking second floor.

302
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:24,667
Okay, good.

303
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:26,967
Let's go.
Let's talk about our plan.

304
00:21:13,133 --> 00:21:14,933
Let's go, love.
Hello.

305
00:21:33,667 --> 00:21:36,533
Good evening.
Thank you for being here.

306
00:21:36,667 --> 00:21:37,467
Hi.

307
00:21:40,367 --> 00:21:41,467
Hey.

308
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:43,033
Girl.

309
00:21:43,200 --> 00:21:44,833
Look at you, Jade.

310
00:21:44,967 --> 00:21:46,233
You're gorgeous.

311
00:21:46,367 --> 00:21:49,167
Relax, it's just me.

312
00:21:49,300 --> 00:21:52,833
Oh, by the way, love,
do you remember Leticia?

313
00:21:52,967 --> 00:21:54,033
Of course.

314
00:21:54,167 --> 00:21:55,800
Hi, Leticia.

315
00:21:55,933 --> 00:21:57,433
Hello.

316
00:21:57,567 --> 00:21:59,200
Love, I'll just use
the restroom.

317
00:21:59,333 --> 00:22:00,833
Okay. I'll be here.

318
00:22:06,500 --> 00:22:08,133
He really is good-looking.

319
00:22:08,267 --> 00:22:09,567
So...

320
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:11,400
when is the wedding?

321
00:22:11,533 --> 00:22:18,367
Well, I'm still taking my time
to prepare for our wedding.

322
00:22:18,533 --> 00:22:20,467
I'm not in a rush.

323
00:22:20,600 --> 00:22:22,033
Because...

324
00:22:22,167 --> 00:22:23,067
Excuse me, Ma'am.

325
00:22:23,200 --> 00:22:24,033
Wine?

326
00:22:28,267 --> 00:22:30,000
Is your name Emma?

327
00:22:30,133 --> 00:22:30,900
Yes, Ma'am.

328
00:22:33,433 --> 00:22:37,100
Get out of my sight before
I pour this on your face.

329
00:22:37,233 --> 00:22:38,467
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

330
00:22:40,100 --> 00:22:42,233
Come on, Jade.

331
00:22:42,367 --> 00:22:44,167
Don't let your night be ruined
by someone who shares

332
00:22:44,300 --> 00:22:46,767
the same name as Emma.

333
00:22:46,900 --> 00:22:48,767
You're right.

334
00:22:48,933 --> 00:22:50,767
Why would I let myself
be affected

335
00:22:50,900 --> 00:22:53,700
by someone with the name...

336
00:22:53,833 --> 00:22:54,833
Emma!

337
00:22:54,967 --> 00:22:56,700
How are you, friend?

338
00:22:58,767 --> 00:23:00,300
How are you?

339
00:23:00,433 --> 00:23:01,767
How's your husband?

340
00:23:01,900 --> 00:23:02,933
Your children?

341
00:23:03,067 --> 00:23:04,667
Damn it!

342
00:23:04,800 --> 00:23:06,700
The night hasn't even started
yet,

343
00:23:06,833 --> 00:23:08,767
and I'm already hearing two
Emmas?

344
00:23:08,900 --> 00:23:10,200
What's this?

345
00:23:10,333 --> 00:23:11,733
Can you relax?

346
00:23:11,867 --> 00:23:13,100
It's just a coincidence.

347
00:23:13,233 --> 00:23:14,600
Well, it better be!

348
00:23:15,633 --> 00:23:17,067
I can't believe this.

349
00:23:20,300 --> 00:23:21,100
Emma?

350
00:23:22,933 --> 00:23:24,933
It's me, Fidel!

351
00:23:25,067 --> 00:23:27,067
Your blockmate in college.

352
00:23:27,200 --> 00:23:29,133
What are you talking about?

353
00:23:29,267 --> 00:23:31,000
Emma's not her name.

354
00:23:31,133 --> 00:23:32,367
It's Leticia!

355
00:23:32,500 --> 00:23:35,567
Sorry, I thought she was Emma.

356
00:23:36,933 --> 00:23:38,233
She's so beautiful.

357
00:23:38,367 --> 00:23:40,133
She was our Miss University.

358
00:23:40,267 --> 00:23:41,500
And she's as sexy as her.

359
00:23:41,633 --> 00:23:43,133
I had a huge crush on her.

360
00:23:43,267 --> 00:23:44,733
Will you leave us alone?

361
00:23:46,300 --> 00:23:47,767
Okay. Sorry.

362
00:23:47,900 --> 00:23:49,467
That freak!

363
00:23:53,067 --> 00:23:54,500
- Everything's okay.
- What's happening?

364
00:24:24,467 --> 00:24:26,500
Logan.

365
00:24:26,633 --> 00:24:28,733
They all seem to be looking
at us.

366
00:24:32,400 --> 00:24:34,033
At us?

367
00:24:34,167 --> 00:24:36,367
Maybe they're looking at you.

368
00:24:36,500 --> 00:24:38,267
You're the most beautiful
in this place.

369
00:24:47,500 --> 00:24:48,967
Yes, Amber.

370
00:24:49,100 --> 00:24:50,967
Yes, Zayn's with me.

371
00:24:51,100 --> 00:24:55,367
It's so annoying because
he still defends Mookie.

372
00:24:55,500 --> 00:24:58,400
That girl really takes
after her crazy mother!

373
00:24:58,533 --> 00:25:00,333
So, so weird!

374
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:03,400
Oh my!

375
00:25:03,567 --> 00:25:04,433
What's that for?

376
00:25:04,567 --> 00:25:06,000
This is the perfume I have used
ever since.

377
00:25:06,133 --> 00:25:09,933
This is cheap,
but Danilo loves its smell.

378
00:25:10,067 --> 00:25:12,500
Do you really need
to seduce Danilo?

379
00:25:12,633 --> 00:25:14,300
Danilo is part of the plan.

380
00:25:14,433 --> 00:25:16,867
Jade must go crazy
with jealousy,

381
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:18,500
just as she did to me.

382
00:25:18,633 --> 00:25:19,400
Emma?

383
00:25:21,133 --> 00:25:21,900
Love?

384
00:25:22,033 --> 00:25:23,700
Why are you looking
at that woman?

385
00:25:23,833 --> 00:25:27,000
She looks familiar to me.

386
00:25:27,133 --> 00:25:28,333
Mookie, I'm sorry.

387
00:25:28,467 --> 00:25:30,233
Let's talk, please.

388
00:25:32,767 --> 00:25:35,200
- Zayn! Zayn!
- Mookie!

389
00:25:35,367 --> 00:25:36,433
Zayn, help!

390
00:25:38,433 --> 00:25:41,167
I feel something strange towards
that woman.

391
00:25:41,300 --> 00:25:43,000
She has...

392
00:25:43,133 --> 00:25:44,667
Emma vibes.

393
00:25:44,800 --> 00:25:46,067
Boss, it's dangerous.

394
00:25:46,200 --> 00:25:49,200
She might notice that you're
keeping her away from Emma.

395
00:25:49,333 --> 00:25:53,233
Hi, I'm Jade Caparas
of Artemis Pharmacy.

396
00:25:54,133 --> 00:25:55,867
The partner of Ramirez Lab.

397
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:56,767
And you are?
